This paper presents a practical approach for processing mobile sensor time series data for continual deep learning predictions. The focus is on machine learning and data processing techniques, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with mobile sensor data, which is often used in Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) research. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the approach in a case study, which suggests that it may belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper uses a recurrent neural network for classification, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the applicability of machine learning to mobile phone sensor data, which suggests that it may belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
